      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Agreed with Dave Ray. You can&#39;t assume that your byte is an ASCII character. You need to interpret the bytes using an encoding. Use byteArrayOutputStream.toString(&quot;UTF-8&quot;) or new String(byteArrayOutputStream.toByteArray(), &quot;UTF-8&quot;)."
    } ],
